"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:10.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">10.1</span> 標題：袋、袋子、口袋、錢袋、錢囊（bag, sack, money bag, purse）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： אַמְתַּחַת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： ’amtachath)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:27\">GEN 42:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:28\">GEN 42:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:12\">GEN 43:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:18\">GEN 43:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:21\">GEN 43:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:21\">GEN 43:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:22\">GEN 43:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:23\">GEN 43:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:1\">GEN 44:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:1\">GEN 44:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:2\">GEN 44:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:8\">GEN 44:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:11\">GEN 44:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:11\">GEN 44:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:12\">GEN 44:12</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： חָרִיט</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： charit)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:23\">2KI 5:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:22\">ISA 3:22</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： כִּיס</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： kis)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13\">DEU 25:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:14\">PRO 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:6\">ISA 46:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:11\">MIC 6:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： כְּלִי</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： kli)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:25\">GEN 42:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:7\">1SA 9:7</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： צִקְלוֹן</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： tsiqalon)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:42\">2KI 4:42</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： צְרוֹר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： tsror)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:35\">GEN 42:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:35\">GEN 42:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:29\">1SA 25:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:17\">JOB 14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:20\">PRO 7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:13\">SNG 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:6\">HAG 1:6</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： שַׂק</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： saq)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:25\">GEN 42:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:27\">GEN 42:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:35\">GEN 42:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:35\">GEN 42:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:32\">LEV 11:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:4\">JOS 9:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： βαλλάντιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： ballantion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:4\">LUK 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:33\">LUK 12:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:35\">LUK 22:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:36\">LUK 22:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob1:14\">TOB 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob8:2\">TOB 8:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ζώνη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： zōnē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:9\">MAT 10:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:8\">MRK 6:8</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： θυλάκιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： thulakion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob9:5\">TOB 9:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： μαρσίππιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： marsippion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir18:33\">SIR 18:33</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： πήρα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： pēra)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:10\">MAT 10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:8\">MRK 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:3\">LUK 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:4\">LUK 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:35\">LUK 22:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:36\">LUK 22:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt10:5\">JDT 10:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt13:10\">JDT 13:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt13:15\">JDT 13:15</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0070_man_with_carrying_bag.png\" alt=\"OAI-0070_man_with_carrying_bag\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\"> (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>袋子是用皮或布做成的物件，用來裝錢等物品。另參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.2.5 牧人的袋子 (shepherd’s bag/pouch)&lt;REALIA:1.2.5&gt;</a> 。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>一般來說，以上所列詞語的使用範圍與中文「袋子」相似。這些詞語所指的袋子可以有不同的大小、材料和品質。因此，它們既可以指裝穀物的袋子，也可以指婦女提著的手袋。通常來說，翻譯者可以使用一個指用布或皮等柔軟材料做成的袋子的統稱。當然，要避免使用專指用塑料或其他現代合成材料做成的袋子的詞語。如果目標語言有多個專指某種袋子的詞語，翻譯者通常可以根據上下文做出選擇；例如，希伯來文<em>charitim</em> 在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:23\">2KI 5:23</a> 中可以譯為「袋子」甚至「口袋」，然而在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:22\">ISA 3:22</a> 最好譯為「錢袋」或「手袋」。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:0\">GEN 42:0</a> – <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:0\">GEN 44:0</a> ，希伯來文<em>’amtachath</em> 指用來裝糧食的大袋子。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13\">DEU 25:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:11\">MIC 6:11</a> ：在這些經文中，希伯來文<em>kis</em> 指商人用來攜帶法碼的袋子。這些經文的重點是做生意一定要誠實，而把砝碼放在袋子裡這件事本身是無關緊要的。因此，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13\">DEU 25:13</a> 可譯為，「你在使用法碼［和量器］時，不可欺騙人」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 英文直譯；原文意為「你包裡不可有兩塊石頭，一大一小」）。另外兩處經文可採用同樣的譯法。</p>\n<p>在有些經文中，可以把「錢囊」替代成裡面所裝的「錢」。類似地，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a> 的第二行可譯成，「我們將分享贓物」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> 直譯），或「我們分享所偷的東西」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯）。</p>\n<p>希伯來文<em>tsror</em> 通常解作「捆、束」，即臨時用來包裝的東西，一般不是成型的容器或袋子。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:9\">MAT 10:9</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:8\">MRK 6:8</a> 中，希臘文<em>zōnē</em> 指人隨身放錢的地方，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 譯為“belts”（「腰帶」）。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 的“pockets” （「衣袋」）和<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jerusalem Bible (1985)\">NJB</abbr> 的“purses”（「錢包」）都是這個詞的文化對等詞。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Bible (1970)\">NAB</abbr> 保留了“belts”（「腰帶」）的譯法，而Brc譯作“money-belts”（「錢帶」）。有些翻譯者會使用一般性的表達方式，例如「錢囊」或「隨身放錢的東西」。不過，這個物件經常被省略；例如，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:9\">MAT 10:9</a> 的最後一個分句可以譯為「你們不要帶錢」。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:10\">MAT 10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:8\">MRK 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:3\">LUK 9:3</a> ：在這些經文中，希臘文<em>pēra</em> 有很多不同的譯法：「乞丐的袋子」（beggar’s bag；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ）、「乞丐的背包」（“beggar’s knapsack”；Brc）、「背袋」（“haversack”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jerusalem Bible (1985)\">NJB</abbr> ）、「包」（“pack”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> ）、「旅行袋」（“traveling bag”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Bible (1970)\">NAB</abbr> ）、「背囊」（“knapsack”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"J.B. Phillips: The New Testament in Modern English (1958)\">Phps</abbr> ）、「袋子」（“bag”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"American Translation (Goodspeed, 1935)\">AT</abbr> ）和「錢包」（“wallet”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Moffatt Translation (1926)\">Mft</abbr> ）。問題是，這個詞在《新約》中可指任何類型的旅行包，也可特指乞丐背的包。由各譯本可見，學者對此並沒有一致的意見。因此，翻譯者可以譯成「旅行包」或「乞丐背的包」。顯然，使徒出去的時候，耶穌吩咐他們什麼都不要帶。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
